# AppPack Development Guide (能力包开发规范)

Scope: all AppPack developers (internal and third-party)

## Pack Project Structure

```
<pack-name>/
├── pack-manifest.yaml          # Required: capability declarations
├── ontology/                   # Ontology schema YAML files
│   └── *.yaml
├── skills/                     # AI Skill implementations (Python gRPC)
│   ├── pyproject.toml
│   └── src/
├── connectors/                 # Data connectors (if any)
├── frontend/                   # Frontend modules
│   ├── cortex/                 # Modules for cortex webapp
│   └── pilot/                  # Modules for pilot webapp
├── workflows/                  # Workflow template YAML files
├── prompts/                    # Persona system prompts
├── eval/                       # Evaluation datasets (JSONL)
├── schemas/                    # JSON Schema for inputs/outputs
├── builds/                     # Dockerfile
├── deploy/                     # Helm subchart
└── tests/                      # Pack integration tests
```

## Development Rules

- Pack Skill endpoints must implement the standard `SkillService` proto interface.
- All Skill inputs/outputs must have JSON Schema definitions in `schemas/`.
- Persona must include: system_prompt, preferred_skills (>= 1), and description.
- Ontology definitions must follow the platform's ObjectType schema specification.
- Actions with side effects must declare risk_level (low/medium/high).
- high risk actions automatically trigger HITL approval — this is NOT optional.

## Data Access

- Pack MUST NOT directly access any database.
- Data read: call dts-query-service via gRPC (goes through dts-data-security).
- Data write: call dts-data-service or emit Kafka events to designated topics.
- File storage: use MinIO via platform S3 API.

## Testing Requirements

- Minimum 50 evaluation cases in eval/ directory.
- Integration test: install → register → invoke skill → verify result → uninstall.
- Frontend modules: basic render test.

## Publishing

- Pack versioned with semver.
- Published as OCI image (Helm subchart + app container).
- Listed in Pack Store (managed by dts-operator).
- Third-party Packs require security review before store listing.
